verbose_text: Nonetheless, there are some commercial subunit vaccinesbased on recombinant protein, e.g., the Porcilis PCV vaccine (MSD Animal Health) is based on the baculovirus vectored expression of recombinant ORF2 protein of porcine circovirus type 2 (PCV2), the causative virus of porcine circoviral disease including the post-weaning multi-systemic wasting syndrome of pigs.
